This test makes sure that the records are added on the same second (since the test already allows mocking the time):

This will fail:
```php
    public function testUpdateIdenticalRecord()
    {
        $cache = $this->getCacheInstance();

        static::$time = \time();
        $this->assertTrue($cache->set('update_record', 'update_record', 60));
        $this->assertTrue($cache->set('update_record', 'update_record', 60));
    }
```
When doing a `static::$time++` after the first assertTrue, it works fine.

